Preheat your #oven{} 220°C. Peel and chop the @sweet potato{1%small} into 2cm
cubes. Spread evenly on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @olive oil{} and add a
pinch of @salt{}. Pop on the top shelf of your oven. Roast until crisp around
the edges, ~{20%minutes}.

> TIP: The sweet potato will cook best if it is well spread out, so if it looks
> a bit crowded and you have a second tray then transfer half over.

Halve, then remove the core from the @green pepper{1} and chop into 1cm pieces.
Peel the @carrot{1} and remove the top and bottom, then cut in half lengthways
and chop into ½cm cubes. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1} into half
moons. Deseed and finely chop the @red chilli{1/2}.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the
@pepper{} and @carrot{}. Cook for ~{5%minutes} then remove to a #plate{}. Put
the (now empty) pan back on medium-high heat with another splash of @olive oil{}.
Add the @minced beef{250%g} and break it up with a #wooden spoon{}. Cook for
~{2%minutes} without stirring. Turn and cook for another ~{2%minutes} without
stirring.

> TIP: Leaving the mince alone allows it to get really brown, improving the
> taste.

When the mince is almost cooked, add the @onion{} and @chilli{} to the pan.

> TIP: Some like it hot, but if you're not one of them, go easy on the chilli!

Turn the heat to medium and fry until the @onion{} is soft, about ~{3%minutes}.

Add the @Mexican spice{1.5%tsp}, a large pinch of @salt{} and a good grind of
@black pepper{}. Next add the @beef stock pot{1/2} and @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can}.
Also add back the @pepper{} and @carrot{}. Allow to simmer and thicken until
there is almost no liquid left.

Once the sauce has thickened, pour into an #ovenproof dish{}. Top with the
roasted sweet potato and tear over the @mozzarella{1}. Place on the top shelf
of your oven and bake until the cheese has melted, ~{8-10%minutes}. When golden,
serve with a dollop of @sour cream{1}.

Enjoy!